title: This Place Gave Me Goosebumps 😮 | Jageshwar Dham Uttarakhand Travel Vlog
description:
Jageshwar Dham is one of the most ancient and powerful Shiva temple complexes in India, located in the peaceful Himalayas of Uttarakhand. In this vlog, I take you on a spiritual and scenic journey to Jageshwar Dham, home to 124 stone temples dedicated to Lord Shiva, dating back to the 7th–12th century.

From the mystical forest surroundings to the deep spiritual energy, this place is perfect for devotees, travelers, and peace seekers. I’ve shared the history, mythology, travel route, best time to visit, and real experience so you can plan your own trip.

Whether you believe in spirituality or simply love hidden heritage destinations, this vlog will give you goosebumps. 🙏🕉️

📍 Location: Almora, Uttarakhand
🚗 How to reach Jageshwar Dham
🕉️ History & significance explained
🌲 Nature + spirituality combined

title: Srinagar Kashmir Travel Vlog | Dal Lake Shikara Ride | Lal Chowk Experience
description:
✨ Srinagar Travel Experience | Dal Lake Shikara Ride | Lal Chowk | Local Market ✨

In this video, I am sharing my unforgettable experience of visiting Srinagar, Kashmir. This journey was full of beauty, culture, and emotions ❤️.

I visited the famous Dal Lake and enjoyed a peaceful Shikara ride, soaking in the breathtaking views all around. I even had the chance to pull a Shikara myself, which made the experience even more special and memorable.

After that, I explored Lal Chowk (Clock Tower), one of the most iconic places in Srinagar. I also visited the local markets, did some shopping, met many warm and friendly people, and learned more about the local lifestyle and culture.

Overall, it was an amazing and enriching experience that I will always remember. Don’t forget to watch till the end and share your thoughts in the comments!

title: Florida Travel Vlog ✈️ Waiting on My First Grandbaby + Shopping & Cruise Prep
description:
In today’s vlog, we’re traveling to Florida to be with my daughter as she prepares to welcome my very first grandbaby 💕👶. We arrived a few days early and spent time shopping and exploring while waiting for baby to arrive.

A few days later, the rest of my kids joined us in Florida, and after soaking up all the family time, we packed up and headed across the state to get ready for our cruise adventure 🚗🧳 (you’ll see the prep and travel—but not the cruise just yet!).

This vlog is full of family moments, travel days, shopping trips, and emotional milestones, and I’m so excited to share this special season of life with you.

title: Raohe Night Market, A Food Paradise In Taipei ||Taiwan Vlog ||Travel Vlog
description:
Raohe Night Market is a celebrated food paradise in Taipei, renowned for its vibrant atmosphere and concentration of authentic Taiwanese street food, including several Michelin-recommended stalls. Unlike larger, more sprawling markets, Raohe features a single, easy-to-navigate 600-meter street, making it an ideal destination for an immersive culinary experience.

Located in the Songshan district, at one end of the market stands the ornate Ciyou Temple, which is beautifully lit at night and adds a cultural dimension to the visit. The air is filled with the sizzle of woks and the aroma of diverse spices, guiding visitors through a plethora of food stalls, carnival games, and souvenir shops. The market is popular with both locals and tourists, offering an authentic slice of Taipei nightlife.

Dive into Taipei's culinary heaven! 🏮 From savory pepper buns to endless noodle bowls, Raohe Night Market is a feast for the senses. Every corner holds a new delicious surprise.

Raohe Night Market is home to a wide array of delicious dishes. Be sure to arrive hungry and bring cash for the most convenient experience.
Fuzhou Pepper Buns: The undisputed star of the market, these are a must-try. The buns are baked in a traditional cylindrical clay oven, resulting in a crispy exterior and a juicy, peppery pork and green onion filling. The stall is located right at the market entrance near the temple and often has a long but fast-moving queue.
Chen Tung Pork Ribs Medicinal Herbs Soup: Another Michelin Bib Gourmand-recognized stall, this dish features tender pork ribs simmered in a light, naturally sweet, and soothing herbal broth. It's the perfect comfort food, especially on a cooler evening.
Crispy Fried Stinky Tofu: Don't let the pungent aroma deter you; this Taiwanese classic is deep-fried to golden perfection, crispy on the outside and soft inside, and typically served with pickled cabbage and a spicy sauce.
Oyster Vermicelli: This comforting bowl of silky thin noodles in a savory broth with fresh oysters is a seafood lover's delight.
Grilled King Oyster Mushrooms: A popular vegetarian option, these mushrooms are grilled to perfection, smoky and juicy, and can be seasoned with various spices like cumin or black pepper.
Taiwanese Sausage: A slightly sweet and savory snack, these juicy sausages are often served on a stick, perfect for enjoying as you stroll.
Visitor Information
Location: Raohe Street, Songshan Di

Experience the vibrant energy of Raohe Night Market in Taipei, a true foodie's paradise with incredible street food options. This travel vlog captures the bustling atmosphere and delicious eats, making it a must-see for anyone planning Taiwan travel. Discover why this night market is a highlight of Taipei's culinary scene. 🤩

Raohe Night Market is a celebrated food paradise in Taipei, renowned for its vibrant atmosphere and concentration of authentic Taiwanese street food, including several Michelin-recommended stalls. Unlike larger, more sprawling markets, Raohe features a single, easy-to-navigate 600-meter street, making it an ideal destination for an immersive culinary experience.

Hours: The market is open daily from around 5:00 PM until midnight, with most stalls open by 6:00 or 7:00 PM. Visiting earlier in the evening helps avoid the peak crowds.

Unlike some sprawling night markets where you zigzag like a drunk tourist on a scooter, Raohe is basically one straight street — which is dangerous, because you can see every single temptation lined up ahead of you. Here’s how my highly scientific eating strategy went:

1. Start from the temple end — that’s where the pepper bun stall is.

2. Move slowly — like, really slowly. Half the fun is watching the vendors do their thing.

3. Follow your nose — it will lead you to magic.

title: 4 Days in Phu Quoc Island 🏝️ | Vietnam Travel Vlog
description:
This week we are in Phu Quoc Island in Vietnam.

Phú Quốc (Pearl Island) is Vietnam's largest island, a tropical paradise in the Gulf of Thailand known for pristine white-sand beaches, lush National Park, vibrant local markets, and luxury resorts, blending natural beauty with growing tourism infrastructure including theme parks and cultural sites like fish sauce factories, making it a popular destination for relaxation, adventure, and family fun. 

1. What It Is:
- Geography: A large island (and 21 smaller islets) in southern Vietnam, recognized by UNESCO as a world biosphere reserve.
- Nickname: "Pearl Island," celebrated for its natural charm.
- Status: A developing special administrative zone with significant investment in tourism infrastructure.

2. Key Attractions:
- Beaches: Relax on popular Bai Sao (Star Beach) or Long Beach, known for sunsets, or find seclusion at Vung Bau or Ganh Dau.
- Phu Quoc National Park: Explore jungles, mountains, waterfalls, and wildlife on hiking trails.
- Duong Dong: The main town, featuring lively day and night markets.
- Sunset Town: Home to the iconic Kiss Bridge, Aquatopia Water Park, and VinWonders theme park.
- Vinpearl Safari: An expansive wildlife park.
- Hon Thom Cable Car: The world's longest sea-crossing cable car (nearly 8km), offering stunning panoramic views of the An Thoi archipelago.

3. Timestamp:
00:37 Incheon to Phu Quoc
01:12 Arrival to Ocean Bay Resort & Spa Luxury Hotel
02:34 Breakfast
03:44 Hotel Tour
05:02 Ong Lang Beach, Sunset
05:28 Dinner at Ocean Bar & Grill
05:46 Day 2, 4 island hopping one-day tour by speedboat
06:06 Snorkeling
06:29 Hon Vong Island (Hòn Mây Rút Trong)
07:09 Sunset Town
07:23 Hon Thom Cable Car
08:49 Day 3, Ocean Bay Resort Tour
11:19 Day 4, Prepare for departure from Phu Quoc to Incheon


*Few tips before visiting Phu Quoc, Vietnam:
- Best Time: Visit from November to April (dry season) for calm seas and clear skies.
- Cash: Carry Vietnamese Dong (VND) for night markets and small shops; resorts accept cards.
- Transport: Download the Grab or Xanh SM app for cheap rides. Use the VinBus (green electric buses) for free travel between major hubs.
- Sim Cards: Buy a Viettel or Vinaphone SIM at the airport.
